post.description:
This operation initiates an FPS standing order in the context of
an application registered with The Bank of London Developer Studio. It takes a request body
that contains all the necessary information required to issue a
standing order.

Standing orders cannot be created for the following accounts:
  - Easy Access Deposit
  - Fixed Notice Deposit

The start date must be at least one day in the future, and it must be a working day. The start date cannot be a weekend or public holiday.

The consumer application (identified by the API key) must always have
the permission to execute payments from the sender's account.

### Example request body:
```JSON
{
  "sender": {
    "type": "TBOL",
    "accountId": "GB-043030-12345678"
  },
  "recipient": {
    "type": "UK",
    "sortCode": "123456",
    "accountNumber": "12345678",
    "accountHolderName": "John Smith"
  },
  "amount": {
    "currency": "GBP",
    "value": 100
  },
  "schedule": {
    "startDateTime": "2024-02-15T00:00:00.000Z",
    "numberOfPayments": 3,
    "frequency": "WEEKLY"
  },
  "reference": "INV-12345",
  "notes": "Additional info for Recipient",
  "idempotencyId": "32ed5f75-638e-454c-a91b-ec16dc8f6e84"
}
